Israeli Stocks: EZchip Semiconductor, Makhteshim-Agan Industries

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-05-05T09:50:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/israeli-stocks-ezchip-semiconductor-makhteshim-agan-industries.html
Israel’s TA-25 Index declined for the
seventh time in eight days, dropping 0.4 percent to 1,287.38 at
12:18 p.m. in Tel Aviv. The gauge has lost 2.1 percent this
week.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  EZchip Semiconductor Ltd. (EZCH)   increased the most
since April 21, advancing 3.7 percent to 107.60 shekels. The
shares of the provider of network processors gained 6.1 percent
in U.S trading yesterday after the company forecast second-
quarter revenue “close to our record revenues in the fourth
quarter of 2010.”  Makhteshim-Agan Industries Ltd. (MAIN)   rose the most
since March 30, increasing 2.4 percent to 18.41 shekels. The
world’s biggest maker of generic agrochemicals said the Ministry
of Commerce of China has approved the agreement for China
National Chemical Corp. to buy a controlling stake in the
company. Final approval for the deal from the State
Administration of Foreign Exchange of China is expected in the
coming days, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in  Tel Aviv  at 
 rgoodman9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  